##  Features
- Interactive CLI shopping experience
- Three store types: **BookWorld**, **ShoeZone**, **GameSpot**
- Five unique items per store
- Cart state persistence (save/restore)
- Multiple payment methods (Credit Card/PayPal)
- Email notifications for cart actions
- Secure review system
- Order lifecycle simulation
- Dynamic discount system

## üîç Applied Design Patterns
| Pattern | Implementation |
|---------|----------------|
| **Singleton** | Manages single instances of store factories |
| **Factory/Abstract Factory** | Creates stores and products |
| **Iterator** | Traverses collections without exposing internals |
| **Strategy** | Dynamic payment method selection |
| **Observer** | Email notifications for cart actions |
| **Memento** | Cart state save/restore functionality |
| **Command** | Order management operations |
| **State** | Order lifecycle transitions |
| **Proxy** | Secure review access control |
| **Decorator** | Dynamic item discounts |
| **Chain of Responsibility** | Stackable discount logic |

## üõ† Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Java JDK 17+
- CLI terminal or Java IDE (IntelliJ/Eclipse recommended)

###  Usage

- Run the Main Class included on the shoppingmall package.
Or
- The jar File included: DP_Project_1242.jar